name: Ohh!One
tag_list: travel, flight, train, bus, railway, india, traffic
overview:
On a long term plan, “Ohh!One” aims to provide exhaustive search on inter-city travel with flights, trains and buses in India.

There will be two divisions of Ohh!One namely Inter-City travel and Intra-City travel.

As the name suggest, Inter-City travel will help you get from one city to another within India via direct or connected routes using .. flights + train + bus.

Example: query : Indore to Bangalore train flight 20 dec 2010 Result : Indore to Bhopal : Train (Junta Express) 4:00 pm to 10:00 pm Bhopal to Bangalore : Flight (Kingfisher) 11:30 pm to 1 am, 21 dec

Intracity Travel Division aims to suggest routes spanning Metro Trains + Bus + Autos in a similar way to above solution. Considers traffic jams, road blocks, damaged roads etc for suggestion.

The website is under development phase and not out yet!!

Fun Facts : Ohh!One derives its name from the pronunciation of “O(1)” i.e. “order 1” which represents the set of computer algorithms which runs in constant time i.e. informally the algorithms which are really really fast!
